your toothpaste.

00:38:56.840 --> 00:39:00.590
I did one experiment all
about cognitive biases

00:39:00.590 --> 00:39:04.520
and trying to eliminate
all my cognitive biases,

00:39:04.520 --> 00:39:06.920
which of course is
impossible, but you can try.

00:39:06.920 --> 00:39:10.370
And one of the cognitive
biases was just

00:39:10.370 --> 00:39:14.480
the routine of brushing
my teeth with Crest,

00:39:14.480 --> 00:39:17.780
because I had always bought
it since I could remember.

00:39:17.780 --> 00:39:20.630
But there is no rational
reason why I chose Crest.

00:39:20.630 --> 00:39:24.290
So the experiment could be just
trying different toothpaste

00:39:24.290 --> 00:39:27.020
until you find the one you
like best, and I used--

00:39:27.020 --> 00:39:32.090
you know, Tom's has a delicious
apricot-flavored toothpaste,

00:39:32.090 --> 00:39:33.020
which I much prefer.

00:39:33.020 --> 00:39:35.810
It's made my life better,
just that little change.

00:39:35.810 --> 00:39:41.720
So yes, I do preach the gospel
of self-experimentation.

00:39:41.720 --> 00:39:42.680
