00:45:41.050 --> 00:45:44.870
So for instance like
with the health book,

00:45:44.870 --> 00:45:48.340
I would wake up every morning,
you know, filled with despair

00:45:48.340 --> 00:45:50.170
that this is such a huge topic.

00:45:50.170 --> 00:45:52.630
How can I write
one book about it?

00:45:52.630 --> 00:45:57.430
But then I would
pretend to be confident,

00:45:57.430 --> 00:45:59.260
and I would act as
if I was confident.

00:45:59.260 --> 00:46:02.910
So I would call my publisher,
and I'd be like, oh, this book,

00:46:02.910 --> 00:46:04.390
I think it's going to be big.

00:46:04.390 --> 00:46:06.100
Let's have a party
when it comes out,

00:46:06.100 --> 00:46:10.330
where we serve kale martinis--
like the healthiest drinks

00:46:10.330 --> 00:46:11.140
ever.

00:46:11.140 --> 00:46:13.600
And then I would call
and set up a bunch

00:46:13.600 --> 00:46:15.370
of interviews with doctors.

00:46:15.370 --> 00:46:18.220
And by acting as if
I were confident,

00:46:18.220 --> 00:46:20.340
after like three
or four hours, I

00:46:20.340 --> 00:46:22.090
started to become a
little more confident.

00:46:22.090 --> 00:46:24.910
